Package: phydynbeast
Type: Package
Title: Configure model-based phylodynamic analyses for BEAST
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2023-11-09
Author: Erik Volz 
Maintainer: Erik Volz <erik.volz@gmail.com>
Description: This package allows users to construct complex compartmental models for fitting with the BEAST phylogenetics software. The model is specified as a list of equations and a list of parameters that specify how different populations should be interpreted within a population-genetics framework. For more information on model syntax, see \url{https://github.com/mrc-ide/PhyDyn}.
License: GPL-2
Depends: xml2 (>= 1.3.5),glue,rlang
Suggests: phydynR
RoxygenNote: 7.2.2
